  "body": "Buidler reports \"Transaction reverted for an unrecognized reason.\" when a require statement is called without an explanation as the second parameter. \r\n\r\nMaybe the message in this case should be \"Transaction reverted without a reason given.\" or something. \r\n\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n`require(currentTime > pools[id].fullPriceLastTime);`\r\n```\r\n  1) Coin Contract\r\n       Price should be fetchable, but 0 since not set.:\r\n     Error: Transaction reverted for an unrecognized reason. Please report this to help us improve Buidler.\r\n      at UniswapPools._priceStatus (contracts/UniswapPools.sol:245)\r\n      at UniswapPools.getPrice (contracts/UniswapPools.sol:106)\r\n      at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:86:5)\r\n```\r\nAfter: \r\n`require(currentTime > pools[id].fullPriceLastTime, \"No time elapsed\");`\r\n```\r\n  1) Coin Contract\r\n       Price should be fetchable, but 0 since not set.:\r\n     Error: VM Exception while processing transaction: revert No time elapsed\r\n      at UniswapPools._priceStatus (contracts/UniswapPools.sol:245)\r\n      at UniswapPools.getPrice (contracts/UniswapPools.sol:106)\r\n      at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:86:5)\r\n```\r\n",
